{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"When I was a student here in Oxford in the 1970s,"},{"time":4000,"text":"the future of the world was bleak."},{"time":7000,"text":"The population explosion was unstoppable."},{"time":9000,"text":"Global famine was inevitable."},{"time":11000,"text":"A cancer epidemic caused by chemicals in the environment"},{"time":14000,"text":"was going to shorten our lives."},{"time":17000,"text":"The acid rain was falling on the forests."},{"time":20000,"text":"The desert was advancing by a mile or two a year."},{"time":22000,"text":"The oil was running out,"},{"time":24000,"text":"and a nuclear winter would finish us off."},{"time":27000,"text":"None of those things happened,"},{"time":29000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":31000,"text":"and astonishingly, if you look at what actually happened in my lifetime,"},{"time":34000,"text":"the average per-capita income"},{"time":37000,"text":"of the average person on the planet,"},{"time":39000,"text":"in real terms, adjusted for inflation,"},{"time":41000,"text":"has tripled."},{"time":43000,"text":"Lifespan is up by 30 percent in my lifetime."},{"time":46000,"text":"Child mortality is down by two-thirds."},{"time":49000,"text":"Per-capita food production"},{"time":51000,"text":"is up by a third."},{"time":53000,"text":"And all this at a time when the population has doubled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"How did we achieve that, whether you think it's a good thing or not?"},{"time":58000,"text":"How did we achieve that?"},{"time":60000,"text":"How did we become"},{"time":62000,"text":"the only species"},{"time":64000,"text":"that becomes more prosperous"},{"time":66000,"text":"as it becomes more populous?"},{"time":68000,"text":"The size of the blob in this graph represents the size of the population,"},{"time":71000,"text":"and the level of the graph"},{"time":73000,"text":"represents GDP per capita."},{"time":75000,"text":"I think to answer that question"},{"time":77000,"text":"you need to understand"},{"time":79000,"text":"how human beings bring together their brains"},{"time":82000,"text":"and enable their ideas to combine and recombine,"},{"time":85000,"text":"to meet and, indeed, to mate."},{"time":88000,"text":"In other words, you need to understand"},{"time":90000,"text":"how ideas have sex."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93000,"text":"I want you to imagine"},{"time":95000,"text":"how we got from making objects like this"},{"time":98000,"text":"to making objects like this."},{"time":101000,"text":"These are both real objects."},{"time":103000,"text":"One is an Acheulean hand axe from half a million years ago"},{"time":105000,"text":"of the kind made by Homo erectus."},{"time":108000,"text":"The other is obviously a computer mouse."},{"time":110000,"text":"They're both exactly the same size and shape to an uncanny degree."},{"time":113000,"text":"I've tried to work out which is bigger,"},{"time":116000,"text":"and it's almost impossible."},{"time":118000,"text":"And that's because they're both designed to fit the human hand."},{"time":120000,"text":"They're both technologies. In the end, their similarity is not that interesting."},{"time":123000,"text":"It just tells you they were both designed to fit the human hand."},{"time":125000,"text":"The differences are what interest me,"},{"time":127000,"text":"because the one on the left was made to a pretty unvarying design"},{"time":130000,"text":"for about a million years --"},{"time":132000,"text":"from one-and-a-half million years ago to half a million years ago."},{"time":135000,"text":"Homo erectus made the same tool"},{"time":138000,"text":"for 30,000 generations."},{"time":140000,"text":"Of course there were a few changes,"},{"time":142000,"text":"but tools changed slower than skeletons in those days."},{"time":145000,"text":"There was no progress, no innovation."},{"time":147000,"text":"It's an extraordinary phenomenon, but it's true."},{"time":149000,"text":"Whereas the object on the right is obsolete after five years."},{"time":152000,"text":"And there's another difference too,"},{"time":154000,"text":"which is the object on the left is made from one substance."},{"time":156000,"text":"The object on the right is made from"},{"time":158000,"text":"a confection of different substances,"},{"time":160000,"text":"from silicon and metal and plastic and so on."},{"time":163000,"text":"And more than that, it's a confection of different ideas,"},{"time":166000,"text":"the idea of plastic, the idea of a laser,"},{"time":168000,"text":"the idea of transistors."},{"time":170000,"text":"They've all been combined together in this technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173000,"text":"And it's this combination,"},{"time":175000,"text":"this cumulative technology, that intrigues me,"},{"time":178000,"text":"because I think it's the secret to understanding"},{"time":181000,"text":"what's happening in the world."},{"time":183000,"text":"My body's an accumulation of ideas too:"},{"time":186000,"text":"the idea of skin cells, the idea of brain cells, the idea of liver cells."},{"time":189000,"text":"They've come together."},{"time":191000,"text":"How does evolution do cumulative, combinatorial things?"},{"time":194000,"text":"Well, it uses sexual reproduction."},{"time":197000,"text":"In an asexual species, if you get two different mutations in different creatures,"},{"time":200000,"text":"a green one and a red one,"},{"time":202000,"text":"then one has to be better than the other."},{"time":204000,"text":"One goes extinct for the other to survive."},{"time":206000,"text":"But if you have a sexual species,"},{"time":208000,"text":"then it's possible for an individual"},{"time":210000,"text":"to inherit both mutations"},{"time":212000,"text":"from different lineages."},{"time":214000,"text":"So what sex does is it enables the individual"},{"time":217000,"text":"to draw upon"},{"time":219000,"text":"the genetic innovations of the whole species."},{"time":222000,"text":"It's not confined to its own lineage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224000,"text":"What's the process that's having the same effect"},{"time":226000,"text":"in cultural evolution"},{"time":228000,"text":"as sex is having in biological evolution?"},{"time":231000,"text":"And I think the answer is exchange,"},{"time":233000,"text":"the habit of exchanging one thing for another."},{"time":236000,"text":"It's a unique human feature."},{"time":238000,"text":"No other animal does it."},{"time":240000,"text":"You can teach them in the laboratory to do a little bit of exchange --"},{"time":242000,"text":"and indeed there's reciprocity in other animals --"},{"time":244000,"text":"But the exchange of one object for another never happens."},{"time":247000,"text":"As Adam Smith said, \"No man ever saw a dog"},{"time":249000,"text":"make a fair exchange of a bone with another dog.\""},{"time":252000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":255000,"text":"You can have culture without exchange."},{"time":257000,"text":"You can have, as it were, asexual culture."},{"time":259000,"text":"Chimpanzees, killer whales, these kinds of creatures, they have culture."},{"time":262000,"text":"They teach each other traditions"},{"time":264000,"text":"which are handed down from parent to offspring."},{"time":266000,"text":"In this case, chimpanzees teaching each other"},{"time":268000,"text":"how to crack nuts with rocks."},{"time":270000,"text":"But the difference is"},{"time":272000,"text":"that these cultures never expand, never grow,"},{"time":274000,"text":"never accumulate, never become combinatorial,"},{"time":276000,"text":"and the reason is because"},{"time":278000,"text":"there is no sex, as it were,"},{"time":280000,"text":"there is no exchange of ideas."},{"time":282000,"text":"Chimpanzee troops have different cultures in different troops."},{"time":285000,"text":"There's no exchange of ideas between them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288000,"text":"And why does exchange raise living standards?"},{"time":290000,"text":"Well, the answer came from David Ricardo in 1817."},{"time":293000,"text":"And here is a Stone Age version of his story,"},{"time":295000,"text":"although he told it in terms of trade between countries."},{"time":298000,"text":"Adam takes four hours to make a spear and three hours to make an axe."},{"time":301000,"text":"Oz takes one hour to make a spear and two hours to make an axe."},{"time":304000,"text":"So Oz is better at both spears and axes than Adam."},{"time":307000,"text":"He doesn't need Adam."},{"time":309000,"text":"He can make his own spears and axes."},{"time":311000,"text":"Well no, because if you think about it,"},{"time":313000,"text":"if Oz makes two spears and Adam make two axes,"},{"time":315000,"text":"and then they trade,"},{"time":317000,"text":"then they will each have saved an hour of work."},{"time":320000,"text":"And the more they do this, the more true it's going to be,"},{"time":323000,"text":"because the more they do this, the better Adam is going to get at making axes"},{"time":326000,"text":"and the better Oz is going to get at making spears."},{"time":328000,"text":"So the gains from trade are only going to grow."},{"time":330000,"text":"And this is one of the beauties of exchange,"},{"time":332000,"text":"is it actually creates the momentum"},{"time":334000,"text":"for more specialization,"},{"time":336000,"text":"which creates the momentum for more exchange and so on."},{"time":339000,"text":"Adam and Oz both saved an hour of time."},{"time":341000,"text":"That is prosperity, the saving of time"},{"time":343000,"text":"in satisfying your needs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346000,"text":"Ask yourself how long you would have to work"},{"time":348000,"text":"to provide for yourself"},{"time":351000,"text":"an hour of reading light this evening to read a book by."},{"time":354000,"text":"If you had to start from scratch, let's say you go out into the countryside."},{"time":357000,"text":"You find a sheep. You kill it. You get the fat out of it."},{"time":359000,"text":"You render it down. You make a candle, etc. etc."},{"time":362000,"text":"How long is it going to take you? Quite a long time."},{"time":364000,"text":"How long do you actually have to work"},{"time":366000,"text":"to earn an hour of reading light"},{"time":368000,"text":"if you're on the average wage in Britain today?"},{"time":370000,"text":"And the answer is about half a second."},{"time":373000,"text":"Back in 1950,"},{"time":375000,"text":"you would have had to work for eight seconds on the average wage"},{"time":377000,"text":"to acquire that much light."},{"time":379000,"text":"And that's seven and a half seconds of prosperity that you've gained"},{"time":382000,"text":"since 1950, as it were,"},{"time":384000,"text":"because that's seven and a half seconds in which you can do something else,"},{"time":387000,"text":"or you can acquire another good or service."},{"time":389000,"text":"And back in 1880,"},{"time":391000,"text":"it would have been 15 minutes"},{"time":393000,"text":"to earn that amount of light on the average wage."},{"time":395000,"text":"Back in 1800,"},{"time":397000,"text":"you'd have had to work six hours"},{"time":399000,"text":"to earn a candle that could burn for an hour."},{"time":402000,"text":"In other words, the average person on the average wage"},{"time":404000,"text":"could not afford a candle in 1800."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407000,"text":"Go back to this image of the axe and the mouse,"},{"time":410000,"text":"and ask yourself: \"Who made them and for who?\""},{"time":413000,"text":"The stone axe was made by someone for himself."},{"time":415000,"text":"It was self-sufficiency."},{"time":417000,"text":"We call that poverty these days."},{"time":419000,"text":"But the object on the right"},{"time":421000,"text":"was made for me by other people."},{"time":424000,"text":"How many other people?"},{"time":426000,"text":"Tens? Hundreds? Thousands?"},{"time":428000,"text":"You know, I think it's probably millions."},{"time":430000,"text":"Because you've got to include the man who grew the coffee,"},{"time":432000,"text":"which was brewed for the man who was on the oil rig,"},{"time":435000,"text":"who was drilling for oil, which was going to be made into the plastic, etc."},{"time":438000,"text":"They were all working for me,"},{"time":440000,"text":"to make a mouse for me."},{"time":442000,"text":"And that's the way society works."},{"time":445000,"text":"That's what we've achieved as a species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"In the old days, if you were rich,"},{"time":451000,"text":"you literally had people working for you."},{"time":453000,"text":"That's how you got to be rich; you employed them."},{"time":455000,"text":"Louis XIV had a lot of people working for him."},{"time":457000,"text":"They made his silly outfits, like this,"},{"time":459000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":461000,"text":"and they did his silly hairstyles, or whatever."},{"time":464000,"text":"He had 498 people"},{"time":466000,"text":"to prepare his dinner every night."},{"time":468000,"text":"But a modern tourist going around the palace of Versailles"},{"time":470000,"text":"and looking at Louis XIV's pictures,"},{"time":473000,"text":"he has 498 people doing his dinner tonight too."},{"time":475000,"text":"They're in bistros and cafes and restaurants"},{"time":477000,"text":"and shops all over Paris,"},{"time":479000,"text":"and they're all ready to serve you at an hour's notice with an excellent meal"},{"time":482000,"text":"that's probably got higher quality"},{"time":484000,"text":"than Louis XIV even had."},{"time":486000,"text":"And that's what we've done, because we're all working for each other."},{"time":489000,"text":"We're able to draw upon specialization and exchange"},{"time":492000,"text":"to raise each other's living standards."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495000,"text":"Now, you do get other animals working for each other too."},{"time":498000,"text":"Ants are a classic example; workers work for queens and queens work for workers."},{"time":501000,"text":"But there's a big difference,"},{"time":503000,"text":"which is that it only happens within the colony."},{"time":505000,"text":"There's no working for each other across the colonies."},{"time":507000,"text":"And the reason for that is because there's a reproductive division of labor."},{"time":510000,"text":"That is to say, they specialize with respect to reproduction."},{"time":513000,"text":"The queen does it all."},{"time":515000,"text":"In our species, we don't like doing that."},{"time":517000,"text":"It's the one thing we insist on doing for ourselves, is reproduction."},{"time":520000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":523000,"text":"Even in England, we don't leave reproduction to the Queen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"So when did this habit start?"},{"time":532000,"text":"And how long has it been going on? And what does it mean?"},{"time":534000,"text":"Well, I think, probably, the oldest version of this"},{"time":537000,"text":"is probably the sexual division of labor."},{"time":539000,"text":"But I've got no evidence for that."},{"time":541000,"text":"It just looks like the first thing we did"},{"time":543000,"text":"was work male for female and female for male."},{"time":546000,"text":"In all hunter-gatherer societies today,"},{"time":548000,"text":"there's a foraging division of labor"},{"time":550000,"text":"between, on the whole, hunting males and gathering females."},{"time":552000,"text":"It isn't always quite that simple,"},{"time":554000,"text":"but there's a distinction between"},{"time":556000,"text":"specialized roles for males and females."},{"time":558000,"text":"And the beauty of this system"},{"time":560000,"text":"is that it benefits both sides."},{"time":563000,"text":"The woman knows"},{"time":565000,"text":"that, in the Hadzas' case here --"},{"time":567000,"text":"digging roots to share with men in exchange for meat --"},{"time":569000,"text":"she knows that all she has to do to get access to protein"},{"time":572000,"text":"is to dig some extra roots and trade them for meat."},{"time":575000,"text":"And she doesn't have to go on an exhausting hunt"},{"time":577000,"text":"and try and kill a warthog."},{"time":579000,"text":"And the man knows that he doesn't have to do any digging"},{"time":581000,"text":"to get roots."},{"time":583000,"text":"All he has to do is make sure that when he kills a warthog"},{"time":585000,"text":"it's big enough to share some."},{"time":587000,"text":"And so both sides raise each other's standards of living"},{"time":590000,"text":"through the sexual division of labor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592000,"text":"When did this happen? We don't know, but it's possible"},{"time":595000,"text":"that Neanderthals didn't do this."},{"time":597000,"text":"They were a highly cooperative species."},{"time":599000,"text":"They were a highly intelligent species."},{"time":601000,"text":"Their brains on average, by the end, were bigger than yours and mine"},{"time":603000,"text":"in this room today."},{"time":605000,"text":"They were imaginative. They buried their dead."},{"time":607000,"text":"They had language, probably,"},{"time":609000,"text":"because we know they had the FOXP2 gene of the same kind as us,"},{"time":611000,"text":"which was discovered here in Oxford."},{"time":613000,"text":"And so it looks like they probably had linguistic skills."},{"time":616000,"text":"They were brilliant people. I'm not dissing the Neanderthals."},{"time":620000,"text":"But there's no evidence"},{"time":622000,"text":"of a sexual division of labor."},{"time":624000,"text":"There's no evidence of gathering behavior by females."},{"time":627000,"text":"It looks like the females were cooperative hunters with the men."},{"time":631000,"text":"And the other thing there's no evidence for"},{"time":633000,"text":"is exchange between groups,"},{"time":636000,"text":"because the objects that you find in Neanderthal remains,"},{"time":639000,"text":"the tools they made,"},{"time":641000,"text":"are always made from local materials."},{"time":643000,"text":"For example, in the Caucasus"},{"time":645000,"text":"there's a site where you find local Neanderthal tools."},{"time":648000,"text":"They're always made from local chert."},{"time":650000,"text":"In the same valley there are modern human remains"},{"time":652000,"text":"from about the same date, 30,000 years ago,"},{"time":654000,"text":"and some of those are from local chert,"},{"time":656000,"text":"but more -- but many of them are made"},{"time":658000,"text":"from obsidian from a long way away."},{"time":660000,"text":"And when human beings began"},{"time":662000,"text":"moving objects around like this,"},{"time":664000,"text":"it was evidence that they were exchanging between groups."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667000,"text":"Trade is 10 times as old as farming."},{"time":670000,"text":"People forget that. People think of trade as a modern thing."},{"time":673000,"text":"Exchange between groups has been going on"},{"time":675000,"text":"for a hundred thousand years."},{"time":678000,"text":"And the earliest evidence for it crops up"},{"time":680000,"text":"somewhere between 80 and 120,000 years ago in Africa,"},{"time":683000,"text":"when you see obsidian and jasper and other things"},{"time":686000,"text":"moving long distances in Ethiopia."},{"time":689000,"text":"You also see seashells --"},{"time":691000,"text":"as discovered by a team here in Oxford --"},{"time":693000,"text":"moving 125 miles inland"},{"time":695000,"text":"from the Mediterranean in Algeria."},{"time":698000,"text":"And that's evidence that people"},{"time":700000,"text":"have started exchanging between groups."},{"time":702000,"text":"And that will have led to specialization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704000,"text":"How do you know that long-distance movement"},{"time":706000,"text":"means trade rather than migration?"},{"time":709000,"text":"Well, you look at modern hunter gatherers like aboriginals,"},{"time":711000,"text":"who quarried for stone axes at a place called Mount Isa,"},{"time":714000,"text":"which was a quarry owned by the Kalkadoon tribe."},{"time":717000,"text":"They traded them with their neighbors"},{"time":719000,"text":"for things like stingray barbs,"},{"time":721000,"text":"and the consequence was that stone axes"},{"time":723000,"text":"ended up over a large part of Australia."},{"time":725000,"text":"So long-distance movement of tools"},{"time":727000,"text":"is a sign of trade, not migration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730000,"text":"What happens when you cut people off from exchange,"},{"time":733000,"text":"from the ability to exchange and specialize?"},{"time":736000,"text":"And the answer is that"},{"time":738000,"text":"not only do you slow down technological progress,"},{"time":740000,"text":"you can actually throw it into reverse."},{"time":743000,"text":"An example is Tasmania."},{"time":745000,"text":"When the sea level rose and Tasmania became an island 10,000 years ago,"},{"time":748000,"text":"the people on it not only experienced"},{"time":750000,"text":"slower progress than people on the mainland,"},{"time":753000,"text":"they actually experienced regress."},{"time":755000,"text":"They gave up the ability to make stone tools"},{"time":757000,"text":"and fishing equipment and clothing"},{"time":759000,"text":"because the population of about 4,000 people"},{"time":762000,"text":"was simply not large enough"},{"time":764000,"text":"to maintain the specialized skills"},{"time":766000,"text":"necessary to keep the technology they had."},{"time":769000,"text":"It's as if the people in this room were plonked on a desert island."},{"time":771000,"text":"How many of the things in our pockets"},{"time":773000,"text":"could we continue to make after 10,000 years?"},{"time":777000,"text":"It didn't happen in Tierra del Fuego --"},{"time":779000,"text":"similar island, similar people."},{"time":781000,"text":"The reason: because Tierra del Fuego"},{"time":783000,"text":"is separated from South America by a much narrower straight,"},{"time":786000,"text":"and there was trading contact across that straight"},{"time":788000,"text":"throughout 10,000 years."},{"time":790000,"text":"The Tasmanians were isolated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793000,"text":"Go back to this image again"},{"time":795000,"text":"and ask yourself, not only who made it and for who,"},{"time":798000,"text":"but who knew how to make it."},{"time":801000,"text":"In the case of the stone axe, the man who made it knew how to make it."},{"time":804000,"text":"But who knows how to make a computer mouse?"},{"time":807000,"text":"Nobody, literally nobody."},{"time":810000,"text":"There is nobody on the planet who knows how to make a computer mouse."},{"time":813000,"text":"I mean this quite seriously."},{"time":815000,"text":"The president of the computer mouse company doesn't know."},{"time":817000,"text":"He just knows how to run a company."},{"time":820000,"text":"The person on the assembly line doesn't know"},{"time":822000,"text":"because he doesn't know how to drill an oil well"},{"time":824000,"text":"to get oil out to make plastic, and so on."},{"time":827000,"text":"We all know little bits, but none of us knows the whole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830000,"text":"I am of course quoting from a famous essay"},{"time":832000,"text":"by Leonard Read, the economist in the 1950s,"},{"time":835000,"text":"called \"I, Pencil\""},{"time":837000,"text":"in which he wrote about how a pencil came to be made,"},{"time":840000,"text":"and how nobody knows even how to make a pencil,"},{"time":843000,"text":"because the people who assemble it don't know how to mine graphite,"},{"time":846000,"text":"and they don't know how to fell trees and that kind of thing."},{"time":849000,"text":"And what we've done in human society,"},{"time":851000,"text":"through exchange and specialization,"},{"time":853000,"text":"is we've created"},{"time":855000,"text":"the ability to do things that we don't even understand."},{"time":858000,"text":"It's not the same with language."},{"time":860000,"text":"With language we have to transfer ideas"},{"time":862000,"text":"that we understand with each other."},{"time":865000,"text":"But with technology,"},{"time":867000,"text":"we can actually do things that are beyond our capabilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":869000,"text":"We've gone beyond the capacity of the human mind"},{"time":872000,"text":"to an extraordinary degree."},{"time":874000,"text":"And by the way,"},{"time":876000,"text":"that's one of the reasons that I'm not interested"},{"time":879000,"text":"in the debate about I.Q.,"},{"time":881000,"text":"about whether some groups have higher I.Q.s than other groups."},{"time":884000,"text":"It's completely irrelevant."},{"time":886000,"text":"What's relevant to a society"},{"time":889000,"text":"is how well people are communicating their ideas,"},{"time":892000,"text":"and how well they're cooperating,"},{"time":894000,"text":"not how clever the individuals are."},{"time":896000,"text":"So we've created something called the collective brain."},{"time":898000,"text":"We're just the nodes in the network."},{"time":900000,"text":"We're the neurons in this brain."},{"time":903000,"text":"It's the interchange of ideas,"},{"time":905000,"text":"the meeting and mating of ideas between them,"},{"time":907000,"text":"that is causing technological progress,"},{"time":910000,"text":"incrementally, bit by bit."},{"time":912000,"text":"However, bad things happen."},{"time":914000,"text":"And in the future, as we go forward,"},{"time":917000,"text":"we will, of course, experience terrible things."},{"time":920000,"text":"There will be wars; there will be depressions;"},{"time":922000,"text":"there will be natural disasters."},{"time":924000,"text":"Awful things will happen in this century, I'm absolutely sure."},{"time":927000,"text":"But I'm also sure that, because of the connections people are making,"},{"time":930000,"text":"and the ability of ideas"},{"time":932000,"text":"to meet and to mate"},{"time":934000,"text":"as never before,"},{"time":936000,"text":"I'm also sure"},{"time":938000,"text":"that technology will advance,"},{"time":940000,"text":"and therefore living standards will advance."},{"time":942000,"text":"Because through the cloud,"},{"time":944000,"text":"through crowd sourcing,"},{"time":946000,"text":"through the bottom-up world that we've created,"},{"time":948000,"text":"where not just the elites but everybody"},{"time":951000,"text":"is able to have their ideas"},{"time":953000,"text":"and make them meet and mate,"},{"time":955000,"text":"we are surely accelerating the rate of innovation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":960000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}